
1)an AP is what allows the wifi device to connect to wired networks

2)a Client is a wireless connection between 2 routers only 

3)a Bridge connects two wired connections through wifi

4)a Repeater takes an existing signal from a wireless router/access 
point and creates a second network off of the existing network

5)ad-hoc is a decentralized type of wireless network that does not rely on
existing networks

6)a mesh network is a  network made up of radio nodes organized in a mesh topology.
It is also a type of ad-hoc network

7)warchalking is the "drawing" of symbols in public spaces to denote an open wifi networks 

8)a rogue acces point is a wireless access point that has been installed on a secure network
without knowledge of the network administrator
